ce simply because it's the most established for being good right now. It's got enough to keep you VERY entertained in every category. HALO is cool, but dont sell for one title. Sure PS2 doesnt have the software, but it's very keen with tricks so the games are still good. Gameplay over graphics is my motto. <br><br>Personally I prefer Nintendo for their oldskool flavor. That new Mario Sunshine looks delicious. So does Zelda and Metroid Prime which (dare I say) looks like it's better than HALO. Before jumping onto the Xbox boat, check out some of the Metroid movies and shots over at cube.ign.com.<br><br>BUT in the end it may seem like your preference will bring you down to a PS2 vs. Xbox debate. It'll be tough, but good luck Kaen!! <p>~Trunxx</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukaenlogos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KaenLogos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/24/02 5:43:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=287.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://genflux3.freewebspace.com/avatar_mm05.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What console should I ask for???</span><hr size=1> thats sort of what its boiling down to PS2 vs X-BOX ps2 has some sweet games and x-box has halo, dead or alive 3, metal gear solid 2 sustanance, several other good ones but then ps2 has good ones AAAAAAAAAAHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH but i will admit gamecubes resident evil looks amazing but ya cant really buy a console for one game and supossedly halo2 is going to feature better graphics than doom3! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utrunxx647.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trunxx647</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WI